Definition: completely and without qualification
Example: used informally as intensifiers; an absolutely magnificent painting; a perfectly idiotic idea; you're perfectly right; utterly miserable; you can be dead sure of my innocence; was dead tired; dead right
Synonyms: adj, all, complete, absolute, perfectly, unmitigated, perfect, utterly, utter, dead, completely, and, without, qualification, used, informally, as, intensifiers, an, magnificent, painting, a, idiotic, idea, you, re, right, miserable, can, be, sure, of, my, innocence, was, tired
Category: adv.all
